      "docs": "Infrastructure-local callable type alias for executing a resolved ref-verifier model request. The callable receives a resolved provider/model execution descriptor and a rendered prompt string; it returns the model's stdout as a String or a RefVerifyError on failure. No timeout parameter: subprocess waits with child.wait() per D13-1/CN-13. This is not a hexagonal secondary port; `RefVerifierPort` remains the only semantic verification port crossing the usecase/infrastructure boundary.",
