    "infrastructure::ref_verify::process_runner::make_ref_verifier_process_runner": {
      "action": "add",
      "role": "FreeFunction",
      "params": [
        { "name": "project_root", "ty": "std::path::PathBuf" }
      ],
      "returns": "std::sync::Arc<AgentExecutionRunner>",
      "is_async": false,
      "generics": [],
      "where_predicates": [],
      "docs": "Factory function that constructs the concrete `Arc<AgentExecutionRunner>` implementation for the ref-verifier. The returned callable maps a `ResolvedExecution` to a hardcoded binary name (\"claude\" / \"codex\" / \"gemini\") and delegates binary resolution to the OS PATH — no environment variable lookup (CODEX_BIN, CLAUDE_BIN, etc.) is performed. Waits for the subprocess to complete with no deadline (child.wait()) per D13-1/CN-13. The returned callable is injected into `AgentRefVerifierAdapter::new`; the cli-composition layer performs only the DI wiring and must not contain any process-management or OS-specific syscall logic.",
      "spec_refs": [
        {
          "file": "track/items/sot-chain-semantic-review-gate-2026-06-07/spec.json",
